#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_cauchy:29
msgid "The probability density function for the full Cauchy distribution is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_cauchy:31
msgid ""
"P(x; x_0, \\gamma) = \\frac{1}{\\pi \\gamma \\bigl[ 1+\n"
"(\\frac{x-x_0}{\\gamma})^2 \\bigr] }\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_cauchy:34
msgid ""
"and the Standard Cauchy distribution just sets :math:`x_0=0` and :math:"
"`\\gamma=1`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_cauchy:37
msgid ""
"The Cauchy distribution arises in the solution to the driven harmonic "
"oscillator problem, and also describes spectral line broadening. It also "
"describes the distribution of values at which a line tilted at a random "
"angle will cut the x axis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of
#: numpy.random._generator.Generator.standard_cauchy:42
msgid ""
"When studying hypothesis tests that assume normality, seeing how the tests "
"perform on data from a Cauchy distribution is a good indicator of their "
"sensitivity to a heavy-tailed distribution, since the Cauchy looks very much "
"like a Gaussian distribution, but with heavier tails."
msgstr ""

